When awarding a grant under § 7-1003 of this subtitle, the Administration shall consider:
The ability of the Program applicant to provide door-to-door transportation to low-income to moderate-income seniors;
The projected volume of ridership;
The Program applicant's marketing and outreach plan to attract riders and drivers;
The ability of the Program applicant to sustain door-to-door transportation for low-income to moderate-income seniors beyond the time when grants may be available;
The ability of the Program applicant to coordinate its dispatcher system with a local central dispatcher system; and
The extent to which the Program applicant encourages:
Shared ridership;
Coordination between public and private sector transportation providers; and
Innovations in risk management for drivers and riders.

In consultation with the Department of Aging, the Maryland Insurance Administration, and senior citizen advocacy groups, the Administration shall adopt regulations to implement this subtitle, including regulations governing:
Criminal background and driving record checks of drivers;
Driver and vehicle safety;
Driver training; and
The liability coverage of a Program applicant that provides door-to-door transportation under the Program.
